result.text:
🎉Five cities from around the world have won the inaugural Global Awards for Sustainable Development in Cities, also known as the "Shanghai Award," at the opening ceremony of the 2023 World Cities Day China Observance on Oct 28.

Salvador in Brazil, Kampala in Uganda, Brisbane in Australia, George Town in Penang of Malaysia, and China's southeast Fuzhou City, were honored with the #award.

In addition to recognizing cities that have made significant progress, it aimed to better advance the implementation of the United Nations' 2030 Sustainable Development Agenda.

During the event, UN-Habitat Executive Director Maimunah Mohd Sharif noted the extraordinary significance of returning to #Shanghai on the 10th anniversary of #WorldCitiesDay. She highlighted that China's "Belt and Road" initiative and exemplary cases from various cities showcase outstanding "people-oriented" practices, providing valuable references for cities worldwide.

@MaimunahSharif @UNHABITAT @EmbaixadaChina @BrazilEmbChina @BrasilXangai @AusEmbChina @FuzhouCity

Our Yang Jinghao boarded the vessels to find out more.
